2013.02.23 <sinuhe@gnu.org>

* Ensure errors and warnings are sent to STDERR.
* Handle memusic directory cleanly.
* Because of the need to refactor the code (and simplify it!), bump to 0.5.
* Release 0.5.

2012.11.15 <sinuhe@gnu.org>

* Change of license. This avoids the misleading and/or clause, and provides
  a liberal free software license similar to the BSD and ISC licenses, and
  is approved by both the Free Software Foundation and the Open Source
  Initiative.
* Release 0.4.5.

2012.07.19 <sinuhe@gnu.org>

* Use upper case tags for consistency with other ripping tools.
* Make sure error is sent to STDERR in mp3cda.

2012.07.18 <sinuhe@gnu.org>

* For now, use ID3v1.1 compliant tagging, i.e. do not record track number
  in FLACs.
* Change release version to 0.4.5.

2012.07.04 <sinuhe@gnu.org>

* Fix a bug in stripmb that caused it to fail to recognize existing FLACs.
* Make sure error is sent to STDERR.
* Fix bug in argument test.
* Remove TODO file.
* Release 0.4.4.

2011.06.11 <sinuhe@gnu.org>

* Be dynamic with leading space removal of tag variables.
* Instead of using options, use arguments that reflect the desired result.
  This includes the removal of -a: this is a FLAC conversion program,
  not AIFF; cdda2wav and cdparanoia are simple enough that a script option
  is not needed.  This also includes the removal of the rmaiff function.
* Remove -m option from mp3cda and make mp3cda independent of flaccda.
* Remove and/or ISC clause, reflecting original ISC license (such as
  used by OpenBSD).
* Thanks to Stuart Jansen for feed back.
* Release 0.4.3.

2011.06.10 <sinuhe@gnu.org>

* Use PID as extension to metaenc files. This avoids multi-user collisions.

2011.02.25 <sinuhe@gnu.org>

* Remove Murray PO Box.
* Fix copyright year in the SlackBuild script, plus minor edits.
* Update manual with reference to icedax, the Debian fork of
  Schilling's cdda2wav.

